1 AN ACT
2 To enact R.S. 47:2058.1, relative to ad valorem taxes; to provide for duties of parish tax
3 collectors; to require parish tax collectors to report certain ad valorem tax collection
4 data to the Louisiana Tax Commission; to require the Louisiana Tax Commission to
5 include the data in certain reports; and to provide for related matters.
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. R.S. 47:2058.1 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
8 §2058.1. Report of certain collections data
9 A. On or before November fifteenth of each year, the tax collector of each
10 parish shall provide to the Louisiana Tax Commission a report of the actual amount
11 of ad valorem taxes collected for the preceding tax year on all taxable property
12 within the parish. The tax collector shall itemize the report by property listed by the
13 parish assessor in accordance with R.S. 47:1957.
14 B. The Louisiana Tax Commission shall include the ad valorem tax
15 collection amounts received pursuant to Subsection A of this Section in each report
16 issued pursuant to the requirements of R.S. 47:1836. In each such report, the
17 commission shall provide the total tax collection amount by parish for each category
18 of property for which it reports total assessed value.
