HB 1010 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Deshotel
Abstract: Requires parish tax collectors to report to the La. Tax Commission (LTC) the
amounts of ad valorem taxes they collect annually on taxable property and requires
the LTC to include this data in its annual report to the governor and legislature.
Proposed law requires parish tax collectors to report to the LTC, on or before Nov. 15th each
year, the actual amount of ad valorem taxes collected for the preceding tax year on all
taxable property within the parish. Requires the collector to itemize the report by property
listed by the parish assessor in accordance with present law (R.S. 47:1957).
Proposed law requires the LTC to include these collection amounts in each report to the
governor and members of the legislature that it issues pursuant to present law (R.S.
47:1836).
(Adds R.S. 47:2058.1)
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Ways and Means to the
original bill:
1. Change the date provided in proposed law for parish tax collectors to report
certain collections data to the LTC from on or before Jan. 31 of each year to on
or before Nov. 15 of each year.
